      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/12545</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;If you just want to avoid that the PDF is displayed inline in the browser and directly downloaded then you should check if the backend sets the&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Content-Disposition" target="_self" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;Content-Disposition&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;Header. Remove it and the PDF should be downloaded. Then the Previous steps can be kept. But as a Auditor I would have my doubs about this outside the system communication.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/re-btp-ui5-app-pdf-file-handling/qaq-p/13854888/comment-id/4881972#M4881972"/>
