    <title>Re: BTP CF APPROUTER AuthType None Problems</title>
    <updated>2024-09-05T08:08:00.296000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>gregorw</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/12545</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Despite the fact that Cloud Foundry would support&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://docs.cloudfoundry.org/devguide/deploy-apps/routes-domains.html#internal-routes" target="_self" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;Internal container-to-container routes&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;the influencing request &lt;A href="https://influence.sap.com/sap/ino/#/idea/255932" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;Creation of internal routes for container-to-container communication&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;was rejected by SAP.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I highly recommend that if your backend exposes private information you secure it accordingly and use the Approuter to authenticate the end users. You can also serve the static content directly from the approuter. That way you can save some custs for the runtime.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/re-btp-cf-approuter-authtype-none-problems/qaq-p/13855167/comment-id/4882019#M4882019"/>
    <published>2024-09-05T08:08:00.296000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
